-- bff-session — APISIX Lua plugin.
--
-- Populated in TASK-0009-api-gateway-spec-to-code. The real
-- bff-session.lua is gitignored. This template enumerates the
-- responsibilities the plugin owns per SPEC-0001 §API Gateway.
--
-- Responsibilities:
--   1. Tolerant Valkey session read. GET sess:{sid} by the opaque cookie
--      value. Missing or expired session → for top-level navigations,
--      302 to /auth/login?next=<original>; for XHR/fetch, 401.
--   2. Bearer injection. Set Authorization: Bearer <access_token> from
--      the session record before forwarding to the Resource Server.
--   3. Hop-by-hop strip. Remove inbound Cookie and hop-by-hop headers on
--      the upstream request so the access token is the only authn signal
--      the Resource Server sees.
--   4. Signed CSRF validation. On state-changing methods, HMAC-verify the
--      X-XSRF-TOKEN header value against the XSRF-TOKEN cookie using the
--      shared signing key (B4).
--   5. Refresh delegation. When access_token is within the refresh
--      window, POST /internal/resolve on the Auth Service with a Client
--      Credentials bearer for the configured gateway client and
--      internal-refresh audience; then re-read sess:{sid}.
--   6. Fetch Metadata classification. Use Sec-Fetch-Mode / Sec-Fetch-Dest
--      to distinguish top-level navigation from XHR/fetch when issuing
--      the no-session response.
